data.title: Bedford County Community Profile
data.meta_description: View names, dates, and locations of the covered bridges in the Bedford County area. See Dr. Knisely Bridge, Hewitt Bridge, Jackson's Mill Bridge & many more.
data.text:
The Bowser/Osterburg Covered Bridge

circa 1890 (estimated) Bob’s Creek, west of Rt. 869, 1.5 mi. northwest of Osterburg, PA

Claycomb Bridge

circa 1880 (moved and reconstructed 1975) 1.5 mi. north of Bedford on Business Rt. 220,

entrance to Old Bedford Village

Colvin Bridge

circa 1880 Mill Rd, accessed from Rt. 30, 100 yds. west of traffic light in Schellsburg, PA

Cuppett’s Bridge

circa 1882 Just to the east of Rt. 96, 1 mi. north of New Paris, PA

Dr. Knisely Bridge

circa 1867 1/10th mi. off Rt. 56, 1.5 mi. southeast of Pleasantville, PA

Felton’s Mill Bridge

circa 1892 Off East Mattie Rd, southwest of Breezewood, PA
